text: Győző Kulcsár (18 October 1940 - 19 September 2018) was a Hungarian fencer. He was born in Budapest.Kulcsár Győző. Hungarian Olympic Committee He competed in the individual and team épée events at the 1964, 1968, 1972 and 1976 Olympics and won four gold (one individual and three team) and two individual bronze medals. He also won three world titles with the Hungarian team, in 1970, 1971 and 1978. He died on 19 September 2018 at the age of 77.Meghalt Kulcsár Győző ==References== Category:1940 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Olympic gold medalists for Hungary Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Hungary Category:Sportspeople from Budapest
